---
import "@/styles/global.css";
import "@/styles/about/exec-application.css";
import Navigation from "@/components/Navigation.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";
---
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="QUT AI & ML Society Executive Applications"
    />
    <title>QUT AI & ML Society</title>
  </head>

  <body class="background-dots">
    <Navigation />

    <!-- PAGE TITLE -->
    <div class="content-wrapper top-space">
      <section class="pink-panel">
        <p class="pink-title">Executive Applications</p>
      </section>

      <!-- INTRO -->
      <div class="info-panel-wrapper full-space">
        <div class="thick-line-behind"></div>
        <section class="info-panel">
          <p>
            The QUT AI & ML Society executive team is responsible for leading the club’s operations, events, and long term direction.
            Executives work collaboratively to plan initiatives, deliver high quality events, support members’ learning and professional development,
            and ensure the club operates sustainably and in line with university requirements.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- WHEN APPLICATIONS OPEN -->
    <div class="content-wrapper spacing-above">
      <section class="pink-panel">
        <p class="pink-title">When Do Applications Open?</p>
      </section>

      <div class="info-panel-wrapper spacing-bottom full-space">
        <section class="info-panel">
          <p>
            Executive applications open once per year at the club’s Annual General Meeting.
            Every executive position is declared vacant and open for re election at the AGM.
            Any eligible member may nominate for a role, and applicants will have the opportunity to outline their interest,
            experience, and vision for the position before voting takes place.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>








    <div class="content-wrapper spacing-above spacing-below">
        <section class="pink-panel">
          <p class="pink-title">Executive Team Roles</p>
        </section>

        <div class="info-panel-wrapper">
          <div class="thick-line"></div>			
            <section class="info-panel">
              <p>
                 QUT AIML Executives are expected to actively contribute to the club by attending events and meetings, taking ownership of their role, 
                 and representing the society professionally. Each role has defined responsibilities and weekly time commitments, which may increase near major events.
                Eligibility requires members to continue their studies at QUT the following year. 
                <br /><br />
                <a class="roles-link" href="https://github.com/QUT-AIML/Constitution/blob/main/Role-Descriptions.md" target="_blank">
                  Detailed responsibilities and expectations for each role can be found here →
                </a>
              </p>
            </section>
        </div>
      </div>


    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>











